      <item>
        <title>Error deploying to hosting</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Johan]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <aside class="quote no-group" data-username="shevabogdan16" data-post="7" data-topic="5046">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="https://community.frontity.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/e0b2c6/40.png" class="avatar"> shevabogdan16:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>On local PC everything working good, which staff is missing?</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>See <a href="https://docs.frontity.org/learning-frontity/settings#site" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">2. Settings - Frontity Docs</a>, because you’re missing the info about your site itself.</p>
<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="shevabogdan16" data-post="7" data-topic="5046">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="https://community.frontity.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/e0b2c6/40.png" class="avatar"> shevabogdan16:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>I’m tried add . htaccess with redirect from every URL to 127.0.0.1:3000 and main page starts work but it’s don’t see images from build</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>So you can access Frontity, but can’t access the assets (JS, images, stylesheets, etc.)?</p>
<p>.htaccess won’t help you, unless you use Apache as a proxy and have the /static/ folder setup correctly in the .conf file of Apache.</p>
<p>Again; more info about the project, the server setup, what is working and what not, etc will help us a lot. Because right now we just guess on what it might be, even when you already tried it or is completely irrelevant in your situation.</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/error-deploying-to-hosting/5046/8">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
